Itâ€™s a great day to code the future ğŸš€

8/8:  One day Ivan released a video on the Aavegotchi game jam and a sort of intro vid into game design using @phaser_ game engine. That was the day I suddenly realised I most likely already had what it takes to actually build something incredible and got to work on @VoyagersGame

7/8:  In Auguest I started getting work for NFT contracts and later merkle tree api's so I set up @peppermintlabco with @henry0eth whom I met during a NFT deep dive to start taking on more work in the NFT space.

6/8:  After bringing in over 10 BNB from this tool within the first month, and over 100 users I knew my direction would become full time web3. For the next few months I started more tutorials soaking up as much knowledge as I could get my hands on.

5/8:  During the first month of dedicating myself to the courses I started building my first project on Binance smart chain. It was a factory using EIP-1167: Minimal Proxy Contract that users could create interesting tokens with a simple form.
4/8:  In March last year I decided it was about time I really learnt solidity and so I started my journey through @IvanOnTech's courses which have now become @MoralisWeb3 Academy. . .

3/8:  I spent the next few years building wordpress websites for hair salons, restaurants, gyms and the like. With any spare time I had I would research and try contribute to crypto projects I liked with UX design which often earned some coins.

2/8:  I started like most self taught devs. A lot of @freeCodeCamp and a front end nano degree from @udacity set me up to start freelancing... 

... I spent more hours interviewing than actually getting any work. I'm sure fellow freelancers can relate.
